"content": "<h2>The heel as a vulnerable part of the body</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:15\">GEN 3:15</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job18:9\">JOB 18:9</a></p>\n<h2>``Lifting up one's heel'' as a metaphor of betrayal</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps41:9\">PSA 41:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:18\">JHN 13:18</a></p>\n<h2>Jacob grasps Esau by the heel at birth</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:26\">GEN 25:26</a> <em>Jacob's name means “he grasps the heel” which, figuratively, means “he deceives”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:3\">HOS 12:3</a></p>",
